    "summary": "Exceptional leader of Biologics and Cell & Gene Therapy business development with sustained high performance over 25 years. Setting up business development teams, creating pipeline growth and deal flow at CDMOs, with large biopharma and start- up biotech. Vast commercial and operations experience in technology transfer, product launches, commercial supply and business assessment for M&A. Expert delivering services for projects for cell therapies, gene therapies, plasmids and antibodies from mammalian cell cultures and microbial fermentations. True and unique global  business leader for CDMO production and service in USA, UK, EU and APAC. \nHigh emotional intelligence enabling effective engagement from shop floor to executive suite.\n\nSELECTED ACCOMPLISHMENTS 2012-2023:\n\nBusiness accomplishments\n\u2022 Delivered and closed business deal for commercial Gene Therapy therapy in 2022, with approval in 2022 worth over $1b.\n\u2022 Delivered and closed 5 commercial COVID vaccines deals in 2020 worth over $ 325m.\n\u2022 Brought Biologics CDMO first commercial biosimilar deal in 2016 with approval in 2019.\n\u2022 Spearheaded $257 million acquisition and integration of a Gallus Biologics CMO business. \n\u2022 Delivered the business deals for +$5 million EBIDTA of small Biologics CDMO site in APAC in first year of operation in 2014. \n\u2022 Team player representing Business Affairs in management teams/boards since 2005. \n\nPipeline development business development\n\u2022 Recruited, started and delivered Business Development Teams across 6 different CDMO businesses, ranging from 6 to 35 FTE\u2019s. Delivered BD talent to support growth of the business, \n\u2022 Built a $1b pipeline with a fresh BD team in 2020/21 during the COVID pandemic.\n\u2022 Grew topline of CDMO with 340% in 3 years on new business to $88m in 2013-2016.\n\u2022 in 25 years closed a high variety of business deals, commercial supply, clinical supply, clinical development, licensing, business acquisition/M&A in US, EU, UK and APAC.\n \nGo-To-market strategies\n\u2022 Implemented data driven targeting and execution strategies for business development team through data analysts.\n\u2022 Redefined marketing and branding strategies for CDMO.\n\u2022 Improved and restructured  the customer journey from first contact to service delivery at 4 CDMO\u2019s.",
